1. type in nano README.md. This will open up a text editor. Type in some stuff and then press ctrl x to exit. Then y then enter. This will save your changes

/*
recruit@umuzi-admin:~/git-basic-exercises$ nano README.md
*/

2. type in cat README.md. This will print your file to the console

/*
recruit@umuzi-admin:~/git-basic-exercises$ cat README.md
Hi i am feli 
*/

3. take a look at the git status again and make sure you understand it

- The file is unstaged due to the changes made.

/*
recruit@umuzi-admin:~/git-basic-exercises$ git status
On branch master
Changes not staged for commit:
*/

4. commit your changes to your repo. Your commit should have the message "second commit"

/*
recruit@umuzi-admin:~/git-basic-exercises$ git add README.md
recruit@umuzi-admin:~/git-basic-exercises$ git commit -m "second commit"
[master a52a088] second commit
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)
*/

5. make some more changes to your readme and make a "third commit"

/*
recruit@umuzi-admin:~/git-basic-exercises$ nano README.md
recruit@umuzi-admin:~/git-basic-exercises$ git add README.md
recruit@umuzi-admin:~/git-basic-exercises$ git commit -m "third commit"
[master edf64f6] third commit
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)
*/

